column1: Sample #
Dyring Notes:
** VORTEX REALLY WELL
** TURN DIALS FULL 360 DEGREES WHEN FLUSHING --- CONSISTENT!!!
Combined OTA 1 3'A-D PCG 2/25/16 in oakridge bottle
First spin in Beckman at 11:10 AM for 15 min at 5000 rpm, 4C.
Rinsed with 20 mL from 50 mL bottle of 1YCM PCG 1/25/16 with 2 mL Cys and 0.2 M NaOH.
Pellet was extra "sticky" after first centrifuge. I had to blast it with media several times before it began loosening.
Tube centrifuged in rotana for 15min at 4C and 6000rcf at 11:43 AM.
Coatings A-L and M-O were made first; while they were flushing P-R were made and hung to dry in the chamber.
Tubes A-L flushed at 20 psi with argon for 25 minutes at the door station.
Tubes M-O flused at 20 psi with argon for 25 minutes under the hood.
Tubes P-R flushed at 20 psi with argon for 2 minutes at th door station.
All tubes placed in their respective locations by 3:00 PM.
Rehydration Notes: 2/29/16
Tubes removed from locations at 11:00 AM
Each tube rehydrated with 4 mL of 1YCM PCG 2/9/16 1 mL 2.5% cys 0.2 N NaOH
Flushed with syngas with green needles at 20 psi for 2 minutes
All tubes placed in shaker at 11:42 AM at 50 RPM and 37C
Tube Q had pressure in it; wasn't vented to the atmosphere fully; popped when removed the cap for rehydration
Assaying Notes; 3/1/2016
Tubes A-L sampled at approximately 9:55 AM and returned to shaker at 10:00 AM.
Tubes M-R sampled at approxmimately 10:50 AM and returned to shaker at 10:55 AM.
Sample H had strange oxygen peaks; rerun with different syringe at 11:00 AM
Sample H had two CO2 peaks come out because of reinjection.
Sampled and run again at 11:15 AM.
Running C, H, I, and J again since O2 peaks
